title: For Sale:  M4 Rail Adapter System (RAS) Forend Assembly w/ Vertical Grip & Panels
postcontent:
M4 Rail Adapter System (RAS) Forend Assembly w/ Vertical Grip & Panels
Made by P&S Products Inc. - Military Subcontractor

Includes: 
1 x M4 RAS Forend Assembly
4 x Rail Panels
1 x Vertical Foregrip

RAS Specifications: 
Rail Length: 6.25"
Overall Length: 6.625"
Weight: 8.9 oz (Not Including Panels & Foregrip)
Free Float: No
Material: Aluminum
Finish: Black Anodizing

Description:
The M4 RAS (Rail Adapter System) was developed for use on the US military's M4 Carbine, and with over 1 million rails issued to date, it is one of the most battle proven designs available for the AR-15 platform. This non-free float handguard is a simple-to-install, drop-in upgrade that features genuine Mil-Spec M1913 Picatinny Rails along its entire length. What sets the M4 RAS apart from other 2-piece quad rails on the market is that it securely locks to the rifle's barrel nut via a clamp and screw arrangement, making it a very solid foundation upon which to mount tactical accessories.

Rifle Requirements: 
The M4 RAS is a drop-in replacement part for standard, 2-piece polymer, M4-type handguards. The rifle must have a carbine length gas system, delta ring assembly, fixed front sight/gas block, and round handguard end cap. Lighter barrel profiles work best (M4 or Government contours). Heavier barrel contours may require modification to the inside of the rail. For AR-15/SR-15 based platforms only; not compatible with SR-25 variants.

Summary: 
My brother (US Army) intended to use this during his deployment to Afghanistan, but ended up using another quad-rail system instead. This is exactly what's issued to US troops with their M4 Carbines. Box and packaging have been opened, but rail and accessories have never been used and are in excellent condition. 

MSRP: $250
Asking Price: $100

Local only. No trades. Cash only.

title: For Sale:  Swarovski Optik 3-12x50 SR TDS-Plex
postcontent:
Here i have for sale is a  Swarovski 3-12x50 SR Habicht PV-N Riflescope during these wee hours of the day can be extremely enlightening. The light throughput across the entire zoom range of this riflescope is astounding. Hunting with this scope is almost like having a pair of aces up your sleeve at a poker game. 

This Habicht PV-N riflescope is a premium optic designed for the hunter who needs the additional light-transmission qualities of the larger objective. Remember, an increase in twilight performance can be the deciding factor in whether or not you bring home the bacon from your next hunting excursion. The variable 3-12x magnification will get you on target at close or long distances. 

The Habicht PV-N 3-12x50 is more than just another sighting system. It's an investment in optical excellence, and a commitment to successful hunting. 

- 0.36 MOA windage and elevation adjustments - 30mm main-tube is nitrogen purged for water, fog, & dust proof performance - Four point coil spring suspension ensure shock resistance with high caliber firearms - Patented zero setting system provides precision adjustment of impact point without tools - Micro-structure grooves prevent residual reflections inside the tube for bright contrasty images, even with back lighting. 

Swarovski Mounting Rail 

The innovative SR (Swarovski Rail) mounting rail system is available on select offerings within the Swarovski riflescope family. The integral fine-toothed rail prevents any movement of the riflescope, regardless of the caliber or recoil of your firearm. Two finely crafted mounting bases with matching teeth engage the rail on the underside of the riflescope for a stable, repeatable and dependable mounting solution. By eliminating the need for traditional mounting rings, the SR system eliminates unsightly & devastating gouge marks on your riflescope's main tube. In order to mount a Swarovski riflescope with an SR rail, you will need to purchase and install a slotted Weaver type rail or bases to your receiver. In addition, a pair of Swarovski Cross Slot Mount Bases must be employed in order to fit the scope to the firearm. This is a precision mounting system and as such it is recommended that a qualified gunsmith install the mounting bases to your receiver for a proper fit and perfect alignment with the axis of your bore. 

TDS-Plex Reticle 

The TDS-Plex reticle is a choice option for varminters and long-range hunters. Four medium length posts and fine cross hairs pull your eye directly to your point of aim. The lower portion of the vertical stadia is intersected by four stepped hash marks that assist the shooter in calculating bullet-drop compensation. No trades on this. i want to fund for a travel in November that's why am selling this scope. Interested buyer's only should mail me.
